{"questionId":"30176830","questionHtml":"<p>Determine whether <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>γ</mi><mi>α</mi></mfrac></math> is a Gaussian integer.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>γ</mi><mi>α</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>41</mn><mn>25</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>38</mn><mn>25</mn></mfrac><mtext>i</mtext></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>(Since&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Re</mtext><mfrac><mi>γ</mi><mi>α</mi></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>41</mn><mn>25</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and/or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Im</mtext><mfrac><mi>γ</mi><mi>α</mi></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>38</mn><mn>25</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;are not integers)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>γ</mi><mi>α</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp;is not a Gaussian integer&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award<em><strong> R1</strong></em> for correct conclusion from their answer.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"30176830","referenceCode":"EXN.3.AHL.TZ0.2b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Determine whether γα is a Gaussian integer.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.13—Polar and Euler form"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}